``` ::: ::: # Origin {#origin} - Lateral head: *crest of pubis* to the *pubic tubercle* @gilroyAtlasAnatomy2020. - Medial head: anterior region of *pubic symphysis* @gilroyAtlasAnatomy2020. # Insertion {#insertion} - Cartilage of ribs 5-7 @gilroyAtlasAnatomy2020. - xiphoid process of the sternum @gilroyAtlasAnatomy2020. # Innervation {#innervation} The pyramidalis is innervated by the [Intercostal nn.]({{< var ref-intercostal-nerves.path >}}) originating from [T5]({{< var ref-nerve-root.t5 >}})-[T12]({{< var ref-nerve-root.t12 >}}) and the [Subcostal n.]({{< var ref-subcostal-nerve.path >}}) with origins from the [T12]({{< var ref-nerve-root.t12 >}}) @gilroyAtlasAnatomy2020. # Action {#action} - Trunk flexion @gilroyAtlasAnatomy2020 - Abdomen compression @gilroyAtlasAnatomy2020. - Pelvic stabilization @gilroyAtlasAnatomy2020 # Overview
